{{Infobox journal | title = Sociological Methodology | cover = | editor = Duane F. Alwin | discipline = [[Sociology]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Sociol. Methodol. | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] on behalf of the [[American Sociological Association]] | country = | frequency = Annual | history = 1971–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.85 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www.asanet.org/journals/sm/sm.cfm | link1 = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal201996/title | link1-name = Journal page at publisher's website | link2 = http://smx.sagepub.com/current.dtl | link2-name = Online access | link3 = http://smx.sagepub.com/content | link3-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0081-1750 | eISSN = 1467-9531 | OCLC = 224478492 | LCCN = 68054940 }} '''''Sociological Methodology''''' is an annual [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers [[social research|research methods]] in the field of [[sociology]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Duane F. Alwin ([[Pennsylvania State University]]). It was established in 1969 and is currently published by [[SAGE Publications]] on behalf of the [[American Sociological Association]].<ref name="Hesse-BiberLeavy2010">{{cite book |author1=Sharlene Nagy Hesse-Biber |author2=[[Patricia Leavy]] |title=Handbook of Emergent Methods |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZimnUvfmE-0C&pg=PA30 |accessdate=25 December 2012 |date=3 November 2010 |publisher=[[Guilford Press]] |isbn=978-1-60918-146-8 |pages=30–}}</ref>
